      <section eId="sec_27_2909">
        <num>27-2909</num>
        <heading>Disposal prohibition</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2909__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>an incinerator;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2909__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a landfill;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2909__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a transfer station; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2909__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>anyone who the transporter knows or should know will either\ncommingle such materials with other solid waste or deliver such\nmaterials to an incinerator or a landfill for disposal.\n  3. No operator of an incinerator or a landfill shall knowingly accept\nmercury-added thermostats for disposal.\n  4. No operator of a transfer station shall knowingly commingle\nmercury-added thermostats with other solid waste or cause such materials\nto be transferred to an incinerator or landfill for disposal.\n  5. Each landfill and transfer station shall post, in a conspicuous\nlocation at the facility, a sign stating that mercury-added thermostats\nare not accepted at the facility.\n  * NB Repealed January 1, 2027\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
